==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ticking
<hw>Tick"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Tick</er> a
bed cover. Cf. <er>Ticken</er>.]</ety> <def>A strong, closely woven
linen or cotton fabric, of which ticks for beds are made. It is usually
twilled, and woven in stripes of different colors, as white and blue; --
called also <altname>ticken</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

